## Definitions

- **Software** DevCovenant in its entirety: all source code, scripts, policy
  definitions, documentation, examples, and auxiliary files.

- **Engine** The core executable code and libraries (Python source, compiled
  modules, etc.) that parse policies, evaluate repository state, and emit
  compliance results.

- **User** Any natural person or legal entity that downloads, installs, runs,
  or otherwise uses the Software.

## 1. Grant of License

1.1 **Non-exclusive license** Apostolov grants each User a worldwide,
non-exclusive, royalty-free license to install, run, and modify the Software
for internal use.

1.2 **Documentation and templates** Users may adapt the documentation and
policy templates for their own internal repositories, provided those adapted
materials are not redistributed as part of the Software.

## 2. Redistribution

2.1 **No redistribution** Redistribution, sublicensing, or repackaging of the
Software (in source or binary form) is **prohibited** without express, written
permission from the copyright holder.

2.2 **No public forks** Public forks or mirrored distributions are considered
redistribution and are not permitted without prior written consent.

## 3. Patent Covenant

3.1 **No patent filings** You may **not** file for patent protection (or
assist others to file) on any portion of the Software.

3.2 **No patent assertions** You covenant **not** to assert any existing
patents (now owned or hereafter acquired) against downstream Users of the
Software.

3.3 **Termination on breach** Any attempt to file patents or assert patent
claims in violation of Sections 3.1–3.2 automatically terminates all rights
under this license.

